## Code Quality
- Use meaningful variable and method names
- Keep methods small and focused on single responsibility
- Use interfaces for service contracts
- Implement proper unit tests
- Use Spring Boot Test for integration testing
- Follow SOLID principles
- Use design patterns appropriately (Factory, Builder, Strategy, etc.)

## Database
- Use JPA/Hibernate for data persistence
- Create entity classes in the model package
- Use repository interfaces extending JpaRepository
- Implement proper relationships between entities
- Use database migrations with Flyway or Liquibase if needed

## Security
- Implement authentication and authorization
- Use JWT tokens for stateless authentication
- Validate input data properly
- Implement CORS configuration if needed
- Use HTTPS in production

## Performance
- Use caching with Spring Cache when appropriate
- Implement pagination for large datasets
- Use asynchronous processing with @Async when needed
- Monitor application performance
- Use connection pooling for database connections

## Always Apply
This rule set should always be applied when working on the Spring Boot project.</content>
